# Python is the interpreted high level machine or a programming language.
# The Python programming language was created by Dutch programmer Guido van Rossum
and was first officially released in 1991.
# Python programming is widely used in multiple things related to Automation, Data Science,  Web-dev, AI, etc...

-- Readability: Code should look almost like English.
-- Explicitness: Explicit is better than implicit.
-- Simplicity: Simple is better than complex.
-- One Way: There should ideally be only one obvious way to do something.

# Features - 

-- Dynamically Typed: You do not need to declare variable types (like int or string) before using them.
-- Multi-Paradigm: Supports Object-Oriented, Functional, and Procedural programming.
-- Batteries Included: Comes with a massive standard library for tasks like file handling, math, and networking.

fun fact 
🎭 It Was Born from a British Comedy ShowMost people think Python is named after the scary snake. In reality, its creator, Guido van Rossum, named it after the famous BBC 1970s comedy show "Monty Python’s Flying Circus". He was reading the published scripts of the show and wanted a name that was short, unique, and slightly mysterious
